Sentencas: This work reports the preparation and characterization of a 3D-printed porous 3 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (3YSZ) inert-supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (MT-SOFC) with high cell performance.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: For the first time, the impacts of pore-former particle size and mass fraction on the microstructure of 3D-printed porous 3YSZ, along with the influences of debinding atmosphere and pre-sintering temperature on the flexural strength and the shrinkage rate, were comprehensively explored.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: Optimal results were achieved using a particle size of 3 mu m and a mass fraction of 30 wt%, facilitating the preparation of a printable 3YSZ photocurable slurry with a relatively low apparent viscosity of 4.2 Pa s at a shear rate of 30 s(-1).
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: Notably, 3D-printed porous 3YSZ debound in nitrogen and sintered in air at 1400 degrees C exhibited the highest flexural strength of similar to 80.2 MPa compared to debinding in air or vacuum.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: Based on flexural strength and shrinkage rate considerations, the 3D-printed porous 3YSZ debound in nitrogen and pre-sintered at 1150 degrees C was deemed suitable as an inert support for SOFC.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: Cells prepared using this optimized approach demonstrated exceptional performance, achieving a maximum power density of 876.8 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, surpassing inert-supported MT-SOFCs fabricated using traditional methods.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance

Sentencas: The outstanding cell performance underscores the successful application of 3D printing technology in preparing porous 3YSZ inert supports for SOFCs, offering an attractive approach for cell preparation and porous ceramics.
Titulo: 3D printing of porous zirconia support for solid oxide fuel cells with high cell performance
